---
import { Code } from 'astro:components';
import Icon from './Icon.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;

interface Sample {
  name: string;
  tag: string;
  tagColor: string;
  summary: string;
  detail: string;
  code: string;
  video: string;
  poster: string;
  learnLinks?: { label: string; href: string }[];
}

const samples: Sample[] = [
  {
    name: 'Touch Ripples',
    tag: 'Touch', tagColor: 'badge-cyan',
    summary: 'Interactive gradient reacting to multi-touch with ripple distortions. Demonstrates pointerCount, pointers, and distance-based blending.',
    detail: `### How it works

The shader creates a smooth UV-gradient background that animates over \`time\`. When you touch the screen, each finger position is read from the \`pointers[10]\` array.

For each active pointer, the shader computes the **distance** from the current pixel to the touch point, then creates a sine-based "hole" effect. The \`mix()\` with a negative factor produces the dark ripple rings.

**Key uniforms used:**
- \`pointerCount\` — how many fingers are touching
- \`pointers[10]\` — xy position + z size per finger
- \`time\` — animates the background gradient
- \`resolution\` — normalizes coordinates

**Try this:** Change the \`8.0\` multiplier inside \`distance()\` to control ripple frequency, or change \`-0.5\` in \`mix()\` to invert the effect.`,
    code: `#ifdef GL_FRAGMENT_PRECISION_HIGH
precision highp float;
#else
precision mediump float;
#endif

uniform float time;
uniform int pointerCount;
uniform vec3 pointers[10];
uniform vec2 resolution;

void main(void) {
\tfloat mx = max(resolution.x, resolution.y);
\tvec2 uv = gl_FragCoord.xy / mx;
\tvec3 color = vec3(uv, 0.25 + 0.5 * sin(time));

\tfor (int n = 0; n < pointerCount; ++n) {
\t\tvec3 hole = vec3(sin(1.5 - distance(
\t\t\tuv, pointers[n].xy / mx) * 8.0));
\t\tcolor = mix(color, hole, -0.5);
\t}
\tgl_FragColor = vec4(color, 1.0);
}`,
    video: `${base}media/sample-touch.webm`,
    poster: `${base}media/sample-touch.webp`,
    learnLinks: [
      { label: 'The Book of Shaders — Shapes', href: 'https://thebookofshaders.com/07/' },
    ],
  },
  {
    name: 'Game of Life',
    tag: 'Backbuffer', tagColor: 'badge-magenta',
    summary: "Conway's Game of Life running entirely on the GPU. Each pixel reads 8 neighbors from the previous frame via the backbuffer uniform.",
    detail: `### How it works

The \`backbuffer\` uniform contains the **previous frame** as a texture. Each pixel samples its 8 neighbors using offset texture lookups, sums the alive-count, then applies Conway's rules:

- **3 neighbors → cell becomes alive** (birth)
- **2 neighbors + was alive → stays alive** (survival)
- **Otherwise → cell dies**

Touch input overrides the sum to 3.0 near your finger, sparking new life.

**Key uniforms used:**
- \`backbuffer\` — previous frame (the state buffer)
- \`pointerCount\` / \`pointers\` — touch to inject cells
- \`resolution\` — coordinate normalization

**Try this:** Change the tap radius (\`0.05\`) to create bigger or smaller brush strokes. Add color by mapping alive-time to a palette.`,
    code: `#ifdef GL_FRAGMENT_PRECISION_HIGH
precision highp float;
#else
precision mediump float;
#endif

uniform vec2 resolution;
uniform int pointerCount;
uniform vec3 pointers[10];
uniform sampler2D backbuffer;

float get(float x, float y) {
\treturn texture2D(backbuffer,
\t\t(gl_FragCoord.xy + vec2(x, y)) / resolution).r;
}

float oneIfZero(float value) {
\treturn step(abs(value), 0.1);
}

void main() {
\tfloat sum =
\t\tget(-1.0, -1.0) + get(-1.0, 0.0) + get(-1.0, 1.0) +
\t\tget( 0.0, -1.0) +                   get( 0.0, 1.0) +
\t\tget( 1.0, -1.0) + get( 1.0, 0.0) + get( 1.0, 1.0);

\tfloat tap = min(resolution.x, resolution.y) * 0.05;
\tfor (int n = 0; n < pointerCount; ++n) {
\t\tif (distance(pointers[n].xy, gl_FragCoord.xy) < tap) {
\t\t\tsum = 3.0;
\t\t\tbreak;
\t\t}
\t}

\tfloat has3 = oneIfZero(sum - 3.0);
\tfloat has2 = oneIfZero(sum - 2.0);
\tfloat alive = has3 + has2 * get(0.0, 0.0);
\tgl_FragColor = vec4(vec3(alive), 1.0);
}`,
    video: `${base}media/sample-gol.webm`,
    poster: `${base}media/sample-gol.webp`,
    learnLinks: [
      { label: 'Wikipedia — Game of Life', href: 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conway%27s_Game_of_Life' },
    ],
  },
  {
    name: 'Gravity Sensor',
    tag: 'Sensor', tagColor: 'badge-violet',
    summary: 'Colors shift based on real device gravity vector. Tilt your phone to paint with physics.',
    detail: `### How it works

The \`gravity\` uniform is a \`vec3\` containing the device's gravity vector in m/s². When the phone is flat, gravity is approximately \`(0, 0, 9.81)\`. Tilting shifts values across x and y.

The shader normalizes gravity by dividing by ~4.9 and multiplies it with the UV+1.0 color channels. The result: different tilts produce different dominant colors.

**Key uniforms used:**
- \`gravity\` — hardware accelerometer gravity component
- \`resolution\` — coordinate normalization

**Try this:** Replace \`abs(gravity - 4.90332)\` with \`gravity * 0.1\` for a more linear response, or use \`gravity.xy\` to offset the UV coordinates directly.`,
    code: `#ifdef GL_FRAGMENT_PRECISION_HIGH
precision highp float;
#else
precision mediump float;
#endif

uniform vec2 resolution;
uniform vec3 gravity;

void main(void) {
\tvec2 uv = gl_FragCoord.xy / resolution.xy;

\tgl_FragColor = vec4(
\t\tvec3(uv, 1.0) * 9.80665 / abs(gravity - 4.90332),
\t\t1.0);
}`,
    video: `${base}media/sample-gravity.webm`,
    poster: `${base}media/sample-gravity.webp`,
  },
  {
    name: 'Back Camera',
    tag: 'Camera', tagColor: 'badge-cyan',
    summary: 'Live camera feed as a shader texture with automatic orientation correction.',
    detail: `### How it works

The \`cameraBack\` uniform provides a live \`samplerExternalOES\` texture from the rear camera. Since the camera sensor may be rotated relative to the screen, the \`cameraOrientation\` matrix and \`cameraAddent\` vector correct the UV mapping.

The formula \`cameraAddent + uv * cameraOrientation\` produces correctly-oriented texture coordinates regardless of device rotation.

**Key uniforms used:**
- \`cameraBack\` — live camera feed (samplerExternalOES)
- \`cameraOrientation\` — mat2 rotation correction
- \`cameraAddent\` — vec2 translation offset
- \`resolution\` — viewport size

**Try this:** Apply a grayscale effect: \`float gray = dot(cam.rgb, vec3(0.299, 0.587, 0.114));\`. Or invert: \`1.0 - cam.rgb\`.`,
    code: `#ifdef GL_FRAGMENT_PRECISION_HIGH
precision highp float;
#else
precision mediump float;
#endif

uniform vec2 resolution;
uniform vec2 cameraAddent;
uniform mat2 cameraOrientation;
uniform samplerExternalOES cameraBack;

void main(void) {
\tvec2 uv = gl_FragCoord.xy / resolution.xy;
\tvec2 st = cameraAddent + uv * cameraOrientation;

\tgl_FragColor = vec4(
\t\ttexture2D(cameraBack, st).rgb,
\t\t1.0);
}`,
    video: `${base}media/sample-camera.webm`,
    poster: `${base}media/sample-camera.webp`,
  },
  {
    name: 'Battery Gauge',
    tag: 'System', tagColor: 'badge-magenta',
    summary: 'A horizontal bar that reads the real battery level. Simplest system uniform demo.',
    detail: `### How it works

\`step(uv.x, battery)\` returns 1.0 when the x-coordinate is less than the battery level (0.0–1.0), creating a white bar whose width matches your battery percentage.

**Key uniforms used:**
- \`battery\` — float from 0.0 (empty) to 1.0 (full)
- \`resolution\` — coordinate normalization

**Try this:** Add color: \`mix(vec3(1,0,0), vec3(0,1,0), battery)\` for a red-to-green gradient. Or animate the edge: \`smoothstep(battery-0.01, battery+0.01, uv.x)\`.`,
    code: `#ifdef GL_FRAGMENT_PRECISION_HIGH
precision highp float;
#else
precision mediump float;
#endif

uniform vec2 resolution;
uniform float battery;

void main(void) {
\tvec2 uv = gl_FragCoord.xy / resolution.xy;

\tgl_FragColor = vec4(
\t\tvec3(step(uv.x, battery)),
\t\t1.0);
}`,
    video: `${base}media/sample-battery.webm`,
    poster: `${base}media/sample-battery.webp`,
  },
  {
    name: 'GLES 3.0',
    tag: 'GLES3', tagColor: 'badge-violet',
    summary: 'Same touch ripple demo but using #version 300 es syntax with out variables.',
    detail: `### How it works

GLES 3.0 replaces \`gl_FragColor\` with a user-declared \`out vec4\`. The \`#version 300 es\` directive must be the **very first line**. ShaderEditor automatically acquires a GLES 3.0 context when it detects this directive.

**Key differences from GLES 2.0:**
- \`out vec4 fragColor\` instead of \`gl_FragColor\`
- \`texture()\` instead of \`texture2D()\` (both work)
- Additional built-ins available (bitwise ops, integer textures, etc.)

**Try this:** Use GLES 3.0 integer operations for cellular automata, or \`texelFetch()\` for exact pixel reads.`,
    code: `#version 300 es

#ifdef GL_FRAGMENT_PRECISION_HIGH
precision highp float;
#else
precision mediump float;
#endif

out vec4 fragColor;

uniform float time;
uniform int pointerCount;
uniform vec3 pointers[10];
uniform vec2 resolution;

void main() {
\tfloat mx = max(resolution.x, resolution.y);
\tvec2 uv = gl_FragCoord.xy / mx;
\tvec3 color = vec3(uv, 0.25 + 0.5 * sin(time));

\tfor (int n = 0; n < pointerCount; ++n) {
\t\tvec3 hole = vec3(sin(1.5 - distance(
\t\t\tuv, pointers[n].xy / mx) * 8.0));
\t\tcolor = mix(color, hole, -0.5);
\t}
\tfragColor = vec4(color, 1.0);
}`,
    video: `${base}media/sample-touch.webm`,
    poster: `${base}media/sample-touch.webp`,
  },
];
---

<section class="section samples-section" id="samples">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-label">Examples</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">Learn by example</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">
      Each example is a full, working shader you can copy directly into ShaderEditor.
      Expand any card to see the code with syntax highlighting, a video of the output, and a
      detailed walkthrough.
    </p>

    <div class="samples-list">
      {samples.map((s, i) => (
        <details class="sample-item" open={i === 0}>
          <summary class="sample-summary">
            <div class="sample-summary-left">
              <span class={`badge ${s.tagColor}`}>{s.tag}</span>
              <h3 class="sample-name">{s.name}</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="sample-oneliner">{s.summary}</p>
            <span class="sample-chevron">
              <Icon name="chevron-down" size={18} />
            </span>
          </summary>

          <div class="sample-body">
            <div class="sample-media-col">
              <div class="sample-media">
                <video class="lazy-video" loop muted playsinline preload="none" poster={s.poster} data-src={s.video}>
                  <source data-src={s.video} type="video/webm" />
                </video>
              </div>
              {s.learnLinks && s.learnLinks.length > 0 && (
                <div class="sample-links">
                  {s.learnLinks.map(link => (
                    <a href={link.href} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="sample-link">
                      <Icon name="external-link" size={13} />
                      {link.label}
                    </a>
                  ))}
                </div>
              )}
            </div>

            <div class="sample-content">
              <p class="sample-summary-text">{s.summary}</p>

              <details class="sample-detail-toggle">
                <summary class="sample-readmore">
                  <Icon name="book-open" size={14} />
                  Read detailed walkthrough
                  <span class="readmore-chevron">
                    <Icon name="chevron-down" size={14} />
                  </span>
                </summary>
                <div class="sample-detail-body" set:html={
                  s.detail
                    .replace(/### (.+)/g, '<h4>$1</h4>')
                    .replace(/\*\*(.+?)\*\*/g, '<strong>$1</strong>')
                    .replace(/`([^`]+)`/g, '<code>$1</code>')
                    .replace(/^- (.+)$/gm, '<li>$1</li>')
                    .replace(/(<li>.*<\/li>\n?)+/g, '<ul>$&</ul>')
                    .replace(/\n\n/g, '</p><p>')
                    .replace(/^(?!<[hup]|<li)(.+)$/gm, '<p>$1</p>')
                } />
              </details>

              <div class="sample-code-wrap">
                <div class="sample-code-header">
                  <span><Icon name="file-code" size={14} /> Fragment Shader</span>
                  <button class="copy-btn" data-code={s.code} aria-label="Copy code">
                    <Icon name="copy" size={14} />
                    Copy
                  </button>
                </div>
                <div class="sample-code-block">
                  <Code code={s.code} lang="glsl" theme="github-dark" />
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  // Copy button
  document.querySelectorAll('.copy-btn').forEach(btn => {
    btn.addEventListener('click', async (e) => {
      e.stopPropagation();
      const code = btn.getAttribute('data-code') || '';
      await navigator.clipboard.writeText(code);
      const icon = btn.querySelector('.icon');
      const orig = btn.innerHTML;
      btn.innerHTML = '<svg class="icon" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg> Copied!';
      setTimeout(() => { btn.innerHTML = orig; }, 1500);
    });
  });

  // Lazy video
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach(entry => {
      const video = entry.target;
      if (entry.isIntersecting) {
        const source = video.querySelector('source[data-src]');
        if (source) {
          source.setAttribute('src', source.getAttribute('data-src'));
          source.removeAttribute('data-src');
          video.load();
        }
        video.play().catch(() => {});
      } else {
        video.pause();
      }
    });
  }, { threshold: 0.2 });

  document.querySelectorAll('#samples .lazy-video').forEach(v => observer.observe(v));
</script>

<style>
  .samples-section {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, transparent, rgba(0, 229, 255, 0.01) 50%, transparent);
  }

  .samples-list {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .sample-item {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    overflow: hidden; transition: border-color 0.3s;
  }

  .sample-item[open] { border-color: rgba(0, 229, 255, 0.12); }

  .sample-summary {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1.125rem 1.5rem;
    cursor: pointer; list-style: none; transition: background 0.2s;
  }

  .sample-summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .sample-summary:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.015); }

  .sample-summary-left {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .sample-name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .sample-oneliner {
    font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text-muted);
    flex: 1; min-width: 0;
    overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .sample-chevron {
    color: var(--text-muted); flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: transform 0.3s;
  }

  .sample-item[open] .sample-chevron {
    transform: rotate(180deg); color: var(--accent-cyan);
  }

  .sample-body {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 240px 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding: 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    min-width: 0; /* prevent grid blowout */
  }

  .sample-media-col {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem;
  }

  .sample-media {
    border-radius: var(--radius-md); overflow: hidden;
    aspect-ratio: 9/16; background: var(--bg-surface);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
  }

  .sample-media video { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; }

  .sample-summary-text {
    font-size: 0.925rem; color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .sample-detail-toggle { margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }

  .sample-readmore {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--accent-cyan);
    cursor: pointer; list-style: none;
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    transition: opacity 0.2s;
  }

  .sample-readmore::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .sample-readmore:hover { opacity: 0.8; }

  .readmore-chevron {
    display: inline-flex;
    transition: transform 0.3s;
  }

  .sample-detail-toggle[open] .readmore-chevron {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
  }

  .sample-content {
    min-width: 0; /* allow content to shrink within grid */
    overflow: hidden; /* contain children */
  }

  .sample-detail-body {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.8;
    overflow-wrap: break-word; word-wrap: break-word;
  }

  .sample-detail-body h4 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .sample-detail-body h4:first-child { margin-top: 0; }

  .sample-detail-body code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.775rem;
    background: rgba(0, 229, 255, 0.08);
    color: var(--accent-cyan);
    padding: 0.125rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .sample-detail-body ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem; margin: 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .sample-detail-body li {
    margin: 0.25rem 0;
  }

  .sample-detail-body p { margin: 0.5rem 0; }

  .sample-code-wrap {
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    overflow: hidden; /* clips border-radius only */
    min-width: 0; /* allow flex/grid child to shrink */
  }

  .sample-code-header {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.65rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;
  }

  .sample-code-header span {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .copy-btn {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.3rem;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.625rem;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.625rem; border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .copy-btn:hover {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .sample-code-block {
    max-height: 400px;
    overflow: auto;
    -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
  }

  .sample-code-block :global(pre) {
    margin: 0 !important;
    border-radius: 0 !important;
    padding: 1rem !important;
    font-size: 0.775rem !important;
    line-height: 1.7 !important;
    overflow: visible !important; /* let parent handle scroll */
  }

  .sample-code-block :global(code) {
    font-family: var(--font-mono) !important;
    white-space: pre !important;
    word-break: normal !important;
    display: block !important;
  }

  .sample-links {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.375rem;
  }

  .sample-link {
    font-size: 0.775rem; color: var(--accent-cyan);
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.375rem;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(0, 229, 255, 0.3);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition: text-decoration-color 0.2s;
  }

  .sample-link:hover { text-decoration-color: var(--accent-cyan); }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .sample-summary { flex-wrap: wrap; padding: 1rem; }
    .sample-oneliner {
      order: 3; flex-basis: 100%;
      white-space: normal; margin-top: 0.25rem;
    }
    .sample-body { grid-template-columns: 1fr; padding: 0 1rem 1rem; }
    .sample-media { max-width: 200px; }
    .sample-code-block :global(pre) { font-size: 0.7rem !important; }
  }
</style>
